## 🤖 3. Reinforcement Learning

### 3.1 Conservative Q-Learning (CQL)
**File:** [cql.py](file:///d:/inventory-quantum-main/app/rl/cql.py) | **342 lines**

**Offline RL with OOD regularization:**
$$\mathcal{L}_{CQL} = \mathcal{L}_{TD} + \alpha \left( \mathbb{E}[\log \sum_a e^{Q(s,a)}] - \mathbb{E}[Q(s,a)] \right)$$

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| **State Dimension** | 22 features |
| **Action Space** | 33 discrete actions |
| **Network** | 3-layer MLP (128 hidden) |
| **PyTorch** | Full gradient implementation |

**Classes:** [ReplayBuffer](file:///d:/inventory-quantum-main/app/rl/cql.py#17-35), [CQLPolicy](file:///d:/inventory-quantum-main/app/rl/cql.py#37-342)

### 3.2 Policy Evaluation
**File:** [policy_eval.py](file:///d:/inventory-quantum-main/app/rl/policy_eval.py) | **10,801 bytes**

- Importance Sampling (IS)
- Weighted Importance Sampling (WIS)
- Fitted Q Evaluation (FQE)

### 3.3 State-Action Representation
**File:** [state_action.py](file:///d:/inventory-quantum-main/app/rl/state_action.py) | **7,855 bytes**

- `InventoryState`, `InventoryAction`, `InventoryTransition` dataclasses
- Offline data generation utilities

